Introduction
************

Purpose
=======

   BDebug is an Intuition controled multi-task system Debugger for OS
2.04 and newer.

   You can use BDebug to debugging your programs, catching tasks,
reseach Enforcer and CyberGuard hits, follow Source-Level Informations
and other advanced functions.  The Debugger supports assemblers, SAS C,
Dice and GCC.

Some of BDebug's features are:

   @{b}*@{ub} font-sensitive, resizable and Style Guide compliant GadTools GUI

   @{b}*@{ub} Object-Oriented that results in a low learning curve

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports 68000...68060 and the FPUs

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports the PPC603/604

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports PPC ELF object format

   @{b}*@{ub} Can debug multiple tasks at the same time

   @{b}*@{ub} Not limited by the amount of window objects.

   @{b}*@{ub} highly configurable

   @{b}*@{ub} keyboard support

   BAsm is a very fast optimizing Assembler for OS 2.04 and newer.

Some of BAsm's features are:

   @{b}*@{ub} 68000-68060, 6888x and PPC603-PPC604

   @{b}*@{ub} Very Fast

   @{b}*@{ub} Include and Incbin Cache

   @{b}*@{ub} Strong Optimizer with Multi-Pass Optimizing

   @{b}*@{ub} High Level Macros

   @{b}*@{ub} ARexx

   @{b}*@{ub} Supports OS 2.04 and OS 3.0 Hunks

   @{b}*@{ub} SAS D1 Source Level Format


