StructWindow
------------

   opens window which can be connected with a structure.  You can use
new structure entries by expanding the the
@{b}<BarflyPath>/Barfly/Barfly.Include@{ub} file or loading a new custom file.
By a doubleclick on a structure window entry you can cause several
actions depending on the datatype.  Every datatype is connected with an
action that is normally started automaticlly.  With the configuration
command @{b}NoAutoStructAction@{ub} you can change this behaviour so that an
action type requester is opened.

   The following datatypes are available.

   @{b}*@{ub} APTR opens a MemWindow.

   @{b}*@{ub} CSTR shows a string.

   @{b}*@{ub} BPTR opens a MemWindow at the address BPTR*4.

   @{b}*@{ub} BSTR shows a string at the address (BPTR*4)+1

   @{b}*@{ub} CPTR opens a DissWindow.

   @{b}*@{ub} FPTR opens a DissWindow.

   @{b}*@{ub} BYTE doesn't cause an action.

   @{b}*@{ub} WORD doesn't cause an action.

   @{b}*@{ub} LONG doesn't cause an action.

   @{b}*@{ub} FLOAT doesn't cause an action.

   @{b}*@{ub} DOUBLE doesn't cause an action.

   @{b}*@{ub} EXTENDED doesn't cause an action.

   @{b}*@{ub} RPTR doesn't cause an action.

   The following action types are available.

   @{b}*@{ub} MemWindow opens a MemWindow.

   @{b}*@{ub} DissWindow opens a DissWindow.

   @{b}*@{ub} CoppWindow opens a CoppWindow.

   @{b}*@{ub} StructWindow opens a StructWindow.

   @{b}*@{ub} NewStruct sets a new structure.


@EndNode

@Node "STRUCTW_Format" "Barfly.guide/STRUCTW_Format"
@Next "STRUCTW_LocalMenus"
@Prev "STRUCTW_Window"
@Toc "UB_STRUCTW"

Structure Macro Fileformat
--------------------------

   This section describes the file format of structure macros.  In the
beginning you define the root directory entries with the first Macro
@{b}Menudir@{ub}.  The first parameter is the name of the entry, then the
address of the parent directory and then the address of the
subdirectory.  In the root directory the parent address is obviously
NULL.  The last entry of the directory is defined by the Macro
@{b}MENUDIREND@{ub}.

     @{b}Label                   ListViewMacro           Link@{ub}
     RootDir:
                             .
                             .
                             MENUDIR                 exec,0,Exec_Dir
                             .
                             .
     MYCUSTOMENTRY:
                             MENUDIREND              CUSTOM,0,0

   The design of a subdirectory only differs from the root directory
entries only by a parent directory address.

     @{b}Label                   ListViewMacro           Link@{ub}
     Exec_Dir:
                             .
                             .
                             MENUDIR                 nodes.i,RootDir,Nodes_Dir
                             .
                             .
                             MENUDIREND              tasks.i,RootDir,Tasks_Dir

   to define the structure directory entries you have to use @{b}MENUITEM@{ub}
and @{b}MENUITEMEND@{ub}.  The first parameter in the Item Macros is the name of
the entry and also the name of the structure.  The second parameter
defines the address of the parent directory.

     @{b}Label                   ListViewMacro           Link@{ub}
                             .
                             .
     Nodes_Dir:
                             MENUITEM                LN,Exec_Dir
                             .
                             .
                             MENUITEMEND

   To define a structure you can use the normal assembler syntax that
you probably have to adjust to your custom needs. For example you can
tell BDebug more informations about the datatype an entry represents.
By redefining @{b}APTR@{ub} to a @{b}CSTR@{ub} you can tell the Debugger that the entry
is a stringpointer.  Another example is defining that @{b}APTR@{ub} points to a
structure by @{b}APTR LN_SUCC,Node@{ub}.

     @{b}Label                   IncludeTypeMacro        Name,Link@{ub}
     LN_Struct:
                             STRUCTUREB              LN,0
                             APTR                    LN_SUCC,LN
                             APTR                    LN_PRED,LN
                             UBYTE                   LN_TYPE
                             BYTE                    LN_PRI
                             CCSTR                   LN_NAME
                             LABEL                   LN_SIZE


@EndNode

