Direct Addressmode Optimizing
-----------------------------

   The assembler can direct optimize certain 68020...60 Addressmodes if
a faster 68000 addressmode exists.  This optimizing method should
always be activated because of compatibility reasons.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}(bd.w,an)@{ub} can be optimized to @{b}x(an)@{ub} that removes 1 word and
     some cycles.

     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |       Addressmode      |     Optimizing     | Option |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     | move. l (1000.w,an),dn | move.l 1000(an),dn |  -OC0  |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}(bd.w,pc)@{ub} can be optimized to @{b}x(pc)@{ub} that removes 1 word and
     some cycles.

     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |       Addressmode      |     Optimizing     | Option |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     | move. l (1000.w,pc),dn | move.l 1000(pc),dn |  -OC1  |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}(bd.w)@{ub} can be optimized to @{b}bd.w@{ub} that removes 1 word and some
     cycles.

     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |       Addressmode      |     Optimizing     | Option |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |  move. l (bd.w),dn     |   move.l bd.w,dn   |  -OC4  |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}(bd.l)@{ub} can be optimized to @{b}bd.l@{ub} that removes 1 word and some
     cycles.

     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |       Addressmode      |     Optimizing     | Option |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |  move. l (bd.l),dn     |   move.l bd.l,dn   |  -OC5  |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}(an)@{ub} can be optimized to @{b}(an)@{ub} that removes 1 word and some
     cycles.  The addressmode @{b}(an)@{ub} can be interpreted as a subgroup of
     @{b}(bd,an,xn)@{ub}. Because @{b}(an)@{ub} is a normal 68000 addressmode you should
     never switch off this optimizing method.

     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |       Addressmode      |     Optimizing     | Option |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |     move. l (an),dn    |   move.l (an),dn   |  -OC6  |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}(pc)@{ub} can be optimized to @{b}(pc)@{ub} that removes 1 word and some
     cycles.  The addressmode @{b}(pc)@{ub} can be interpreted as a subgroup of
     @{b}(bd,pc,xn)@{ub}. Because @{b}(pc)@{ub} is a normal 68000 addressmode you should
     never switch off this optimizing method.

     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |       Addressmode      |     Optimizing     | Option |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+
     |     move. l (pc),dn    |   move.l (pc),dn   |  -OC7  |
     +------------------------+--------------------+--------+


@EndNode

